<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>FAN DRIVE CLUTCH: KYSOR 1090 (8000 SERIES) - OPERATION - COMBINATION OF BASIC SYSTEM WITH AIR CONDITIONING
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="2">
        <title>COMBINATION OF BASIC SYSTEM WITH AIR CONDITIONING</title>
        <para>Adding air conditioning puts another normally closed switch in the system to provide cooling necessary to
            protect the A/C compressor from excessive head pressure (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1200103">Figure 3</hotlnk>and
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1200104">Figure 4</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f1200103" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1200103" filename="../figg12/G1200103.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 3. Basic System with Air Conditioning</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1.VEHICLE GROUND</callout1>
                <callout1>2.FAN SOLENOID (NC)</callout1>
                <callout1>3.FAN FREON PRESSURE SWITCH</callout1>
                <callout1>4.(1) TERMINAL</callout1>
                <callout1>5.THERMAL SWITCH (NC)</callout1>
                <callout1>6.IGNITION VOLTAGE SOURCE</callout1>
                <callout1>7.(+) TERMINAL</callout1>
                <callout1>8.SHUTTER FREON PRESSURE SWITCH</callout1>
                <callout1>9.SHUTTER SOLENOID (NC)</callout1>
                <callout1>10.A/C COMPRESSOR</callout1>
                <callout1>11.COMPRESSOR TO CONDENSER HOSE</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1200104" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1200104" filename="../figg12/G1200104.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 4. Basic System with Air Conditioning and Shutters</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The refrigerant switch measures A/C compressor head pressure. The switch is in series with the fan control
            Alarmstat and the fan clutch solenoid. If the compressor head pressure exceeds 300 psi +/- 10 psi, the
            switch will open and turn on the fan. When the head pressure drops to less than 210 psi +/- 10 psi, the
            switch closes and the fan is disengaged.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
